Tested byTestaro, procedure ts24
Scored byTestilo, procedure tsp24
Digested byTestilo, procedure tdp24

Introduction

This is a digest of results from a battery of accessibility Tests.

The battery includes 1353 automated accessibility tests drawn from ten different packages: Alfa, Axe, Continuum, Equal Access, HTML CodeSniffer, Nu Html Checker, QualWeb, Tenon, Testaro, and WAVE.

These tests were run on the web page named above and gave the page a score of 3068, where 0 would be perfect.

Issue summary

Special issues

log: Score 814. This is based on the amount of browser error logging and miscellaneous logging during the tests.

preventions: Score 100. This is based on tests that the page did not allow to be run. That impedes accessibility progress and risks interfering with tools that users with disabilities need.

Classified issues

Issue parentMissing

WCAG: 1.3.1

Score: 268

Issue reports in this category:

  • Package alfa, test r42, score 196 (Element is not owned by an element of its required context role)
  • Package axe, test aria-required-parent, score 176 (ARIA role is not contained by a required parent)

Issue contentBeyondLandmarks

WCAG: 1.3.6

Score: 239

Issue reports in this category:

  • Package alfa, test r57, score 182 (Perceivable text content is not included in any landmark)
  • Package axe, test region, score 30 (Some page content is not contained by landmarks)
  • Package ibm, test Rpt_Aria_OrphanedContent_Native_Host_Sematics, score 108 (Content does not reside within an element with a landmark role)

Issue textContrastAA

WCAG: 1.4.3

Score: 198

Issue reports in this category:

  • Package alfa, test r69, score 154 (Text outside widget has subminimum contrast)
  • Package axe, test color-contrast, score 28 (Element has insufficient color contrast)
  • Package ibm, test IBMA_Color_Contrast_WCAG2AA, score 40 (Contrast ratio of text with background does not meet WCAG 2.1 AA)
  • Package wave, test c:contrast, score 36 (Very low contrast)

Score: 176
